<br>
Yes, sometimes God is simple, but there is also much about Him that is mysterious and miraculous.<br>
<br>
The presence of Christ in the Eucharist, for those who believe that, is a Holy Mystery of Faith.<br>
<br>
Similar to when we say, Christ has died, Christ is risen, Christ will come again, this is also a miraculous mystery, and one we proclaim willingly in faith.<br>
<br>
I know that it doesn't seem to make logical sense that the wine still tastes like wine, or the bread like bread, but I still believe that the core substance is the body and blood of our Lord.<br>
